ej,coopc001,M,mosec901,Call at 1B $Jeff Keppinger's gounder was bobbled by Orlando Hudson, who picked up the ball and threw to first; Keppinger was called out by 1B umpire Casey Moser on a very close play; the Astros bench exploded, Keppinger yelled at Moser, but was restrained by 1B coach Jose Cruz; Astros manager Cecil Cooper argued with Moser and was ejected very quickly
Dodgers second baseman Orlando Hudson left the game due to an injured hand/wrist

replay,1,tavew001,CIN,laynj901,LOS03,O,N,I,,H $Willy Tavaras hit a ball at the top of the fence, which was ruled in play; Reds manager Dusty Baker argued that it should be a home run; acting crew chief Jerry Layne watched the replay and upheld the call

ej,motag001,P,barkl901,Intentional HBP $Prince Fielder stared at Dodgers pitcher Guillermo Mota, who was immediately ejected by HP umpire Lance Barksdale; two Dodgers had been hit earlier and the score was 17-4; Fielder was escorted to 1B by crew chief Randy Marsh and 1B coach Ed Sedar; after the game Fielder tried to get into the Dodger club house but was denied admission by security personnel; two teammates took Fielder back to the Brewers club house

ej,cox-b103,M,coope901,Confusing call on pitch during steal $HP umpire Eric Cooper appeared to call a strike to Andre Ethier on the outside corner as Rafael Furcal was attempting to steal 2B; as 2B umpire Chuck Meriwether called Furcal out at 2B, Cooper called time, saying that the pitch was ball four; Braves manager Bobby Cox argued with Cooper and Cox kept making a strike call with his right arm imitating Cooper's motion; Cox was ejected by Cooper
